#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
preflight-check — Script 1 of 5 for the ClarityRev 25-niche evaluation pipeline.

Google SRE pattern: software engineering for operations.
Stripe API design: contract-first. Netflix Chaos Engineering: assume failure.

Determines whether a credit-consuming fetch operation should proceed.
Three questions answered before any credit burn:
  1. Is fresh data already cached?       -> SKIP (save credits)
  2. Are sufficient credits available?   -> BLOCK if below threshold
  3. Is the target host dead?            -> BLOCK if in dead-host registry

Usage:
    ./preflight-check NICHE_ID DATA_TYPE [--target-url URL] [--dry-run]

Exit codes:
    0  SUCCESS        - All checks passed (PROCEED) or fresh cache found (SKIP_CACHE_HIT)
    1  BLOCKED        - Blocking issue (insufficient credits or dead host)
    2  WARNING        - Non-blocking issue, proceed with caution
    3  INTERNAL_ERROR - Script itself failed (bug, missing dep, corrupted file)
    4  INVALID_INPUT  - Arguments or input files malformed
"""

